---
import Layout from "../layouts/layouts.astro";
import PhotoPlaceholder from "../components/PhotoPlaceholder.astro";
---

<Layout title="Quick Start | Nardelli">
	<section class="hero">
		<h1>Quick Start</h1>
		<p class="subhead">
			The essentials for arriving, getting set up, and settling in during your first 10 minutes.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Address</h2>
		<div class="callout">
			<strong>Nardelli Nespolo</strong><br />
			Località Nardelli, 31, 06061 Nardelli PG, Italy
		</div>
		<!-- Optional later: add an "Open in Google Maps" link here -->
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Parking</h2>
		<p>
			Please park close to the front door. <strong>Do not block the laneway at the side of the house</strong>
			— this access route is needed for neighbours and farming access.
		</p>
		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Parking near the front door + ‘do not block laneway’" />
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Keys (lockbox)</h2>
		<p>
			There is a lockbox attached to the frame of the garden gate. It contains the key to the{" "}
			<strong>front door</strong> and the <strong>garden gate</strong>. You already have the code.
		</p>

		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Front door key tip:</strong> to remove the key from the front door, you may need to turn it{" "}
				<strong>half a turn back</strong> first.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Please leave the garden key in the lockbox</strong> (and scramble the lockbox code) unless
				you are using it — the gardener may need access.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Lockbox location + keys" />
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Electricity (power)</h2>
		<p>
			The electricity will most likely be off on arrival. The fuse box is located <strong>just inside the front
			door</strong>, on the wall as you enter the kitchen. Flick the switch <strong>up</strong> to turn the
			power on.
		</p>
		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Fuse box + switch in the ON position" />
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Water &amp; gas (mains)</h2>
		<p>
			On arrival, the <strong>water and gas mains may be switched off</strong>. The key to open the mains
			access is on a key hanger just inside the front door.
		</p>

		<ol>
			<li>Open the Gas and Water mains access at the front of the house using the key.</li>
			<li>Ensure both the <strong>gas</strong> and <strong>water</strong> are switched to the <strong>ON</strong> position.</li>
			<li>
				Once on, check the water flow, check hot water, and confirm the hob is working.
			</li>
		</ol>

		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Gas mains — ON position" />
		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Water mains — ON position" />

		<h3>Hot water (boiler)</h3>
		<p>
			The button for the boiler is on the wall <strong>between the sink and the fridge</strong>. Once the mains
			are on, check that hot water is working.
		</p>
		<PhotoPlaceholder label="Boiler / hot water button (between sink and fridge)" />
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Windows &amp; shutters (mosquito nets)</h2>
		<p>
			Windows and shutters open from the inside. There is netting on the window frames to help keep out
			mosquitos.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Lift/peel the net slightly from one corner to access the shutter latch.</li>
			<li>Open the shutter, then re-cover the frame with the netting.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			If you’re not visiting in July/August, windows and fans may be all that’s needed to cool the house down
			in the evenings.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Air conditioning &amp; fans</h2>
		<p>
			There are portable air-con units in all rooms. Ensure the hose/cylinder at the back of the unit is
			connected to the wall vent so hot air is directed outside.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Tip:</strong> If all units are on at the same time (upstairs and downstairs), it can blow the
			fuse. We recommend not running all units simultaneously. There are multiple fans you can use to
			supplement.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Internet (Wi‑Fi)</h2>
		<p>
			There is <strong>no Wi‑Fi</strong> in the house and mobile reception varies by provider. If you struggle
			for internet, consider an Italian eSIM (e.g. via Revolut or directly with a provider) after arriving.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Garden</h2>
		<p>
			You can access the garden via the sitting room (keys either by the back door or with the keys by the
			front door), or through the garden gate at the front of the house.
		</p>
		<p>
			There are tables and chairs, clothes horses, and a paddling pool that can be used in the garden. If
			it’s dry, please water the garden in the mornings or evenings if you can.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Rubbish bins &amp; recycling</h2>
		<p>
			We don’t have scheduled bin collections, so we tend to empty the bins regularly and recycle bottles and
			other items as we go.
		</p>
		<p>
			We normally use the recycling and bins at the <strong>COOP supermarket</strong> or near the car park by{" "}
			<strong>Pescatore Cafe</strong> (these are good bins to use).
		</p>
		<!-- Optional later: add a small map link or a pin reference on your Essentials map -->
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Neighbours</h2>
		<p>
			We have lots of lovely neighbours in Nardelli from different parts of Italy, the UK and the US. Please
			say hello — you can find their names and details on the neighbours map on the{" "}
			<a href="/house">Our House &amp; Neighbours</a> page.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<h2>Contact</h2>
		<p>
			If you have any issues at all, please message or call any of the family on <strong>WhatsApp</strong>.
		</p>
		<!-- Optional later: add specific names + numbers here -->
	</section>

	<style>
		.hero { margin-bottom: 12px; }
		.subhead { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; margin-top: -6px; }

		.section { margin-top: 22px; }
		h2 { margin-bottom: 8px; }
		h3 { margin-top: 18px; margin-bottom: 6px; }

		.callout {
			background: var(--card);
			border: 1px solid var(--border);
			border-radius: var(--radius);
			padding: 14px;
		}

		.photo {
			margin-top: 10px;
			border: 1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, var(--border) 70%, var(--accent) 30%);
			border-radius: var(--radius);
			background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg) 70%, var(--card) 30%);
			padding: 12px;
		}

		.photoInner {
			display: grid;
			gap: 4px;
		}

		.photoTitle {
			font-weight: 800;
			color: var(--accentHover);
			font-size: 13px;
			letter-spacing: 0.02em;
			text-transform: uppercase;
		}

		.photoLabel {
			color: var(--muted);
			font-weight: 600;
			font-size: 14px;
		}

		/* Keep lists readable on mobile */
		ul, ol { padding-left: 20px; }
		li { margin: 6px 0; }
	</style>
</Layout>